twork.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":58},"#text_condition.complete",{"lettering":60,"dimensions":61},"Elegant letters, of a regular size, tending to a slightly curving form, with M and A tending towards cursive forms. I in line 1 and Y in line 3 both extravagant and tall. Use of elegant hederae.",[62,69],{"type":63,"l":64,"from":65,"to":66,"h":67,"unit":68},"letterHeight","Line 1-4","line1","line4","25","mm",{"type":70,"l":71,"from":65,"to":72,"unit":68},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2",{"_":74,"notBefore":75,"notAfter":76,"evidence":77},"The necropolis material dates C1 CE to mid-C2 CE; the lettering is more likely C2 CE",51,151,"archaeological-context, textual-context",[79],{"_":80,"type":81,"ref":82,"region":83},"Cuticchi","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/8977891","Sicilia",[85],[86,87],37.5454,14.51691,{"_":89,"type":90,"subtype":91,"when":92,"geo":93},"Found in archaeological excavation of a rural settlement and extensive necropolis in the area of contrada Cuticchi (in the context of railway construction work). The urn was found in situ in T.16, a fossa burial ,covered with terracotta slabs.","found","discovered","2022",null,[],{"_":96,"type":97,"subtype":98,"geo":93},"None.","observed","autopsied",[100],{"n":101,"url":102,"height":103,"width":104,"desc":105,"surfaceType":106},"screen","ISic001693_tiled.tif","1147px","999px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo (c) Soprintendenza per i Beni Culturali e Ambientali di Enna","front","Sicily","Enna",{"_":110,"role":111},"Soprintendenza per i Beni Culturali e Ambientali di Enna","store",{"type":113},"inventory",{"_":115,"mainLang":116,"languages":117},"Latin","la",[115],{"type":119,"bibl":120},"edition",[121],{"author":122,"date":123,"citedRange":124,"ptr":125,"inscriptionDate":123,"year":127},"Merendino et al.","2025","146-147, fig.10.24",{"target":126},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/CM7T8P48","",{"type":129,"bibl":130},"discussion",[93],{"editor":132,"principal":134,"contributors":135,"change":137},{"_":19,"ref":133},"#JP",{"_":19,"ref":133},[136],{"_":19,"xml:id":20,"ref":21},{"_":138,"when":139,"who":133},"Jonathan Prag created file from publication","2025-12-17",{"n":101,"url":102,"height":103,"width":104,"desc":105,"surfaceType":106},[],[143],"Merendino et al., 2025",[145],"CM7T8P48",[147,148,149,24,29,33,150,151,152,153,154,155,116],"isic001693","funerary urn for chius",{"_":5},"cuticchi","sicilia","sicily","enna","soprintendenza per i beni culturali e ambientali di enna","latin",[],{"title":158,"body":159,"divs":160,"editions":187,"images":197,"handnote":203},"ISic001693. Funerary urn for Chius","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: #JP\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Chio\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Chio\">Chio\u003C/span>\u003C/span> ❦ mag(no) mag(istri) \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>pec(oris) ❦ vix(it) ❦ an(nos) ❦ XXXV \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Hesychus\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Hesychus\">Hesychus\u003C/span>\u003C/span> ❦ disp(ensator) \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>fecit \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: #JP\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Chio\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Chio\">CHIO\u003C/span>\u003C/span>❦MAGMAG\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>PEC❦VIX❦AN❦XXXV\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Hesychus\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Hesychus\">HESYCHUS\u003C/span>\u003C/span>❦DISP\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>FECIT\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001693_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo (c) Soprintendenza per i Beni Culturali e Ambientali di Enna\" src=\"ISic001693_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001693.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo (c) Soprintendenza per i Beni Culturali e Ambientali di Enna\" src=\"ISic001693-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text from photograph\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>For Chius, chief overseer of the herds. He lived 35 years. Hesychus the steward made it.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>A similar text, a funerary epitaph for Abdalas, magnus magister ovium (i.e. sheep) (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000628\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000628\u003C/a>) was found some 16 km SE of this site. Abdalas was a slave of Domitia Longina, wife of the Emperor Domitian, and a similar context, of either imperial estates or another elite wealthy landowner is likely. \u003Ca href=\"http://data.perseus.org/citations/urn:cts:latinLit:phi0474.phi005.perseus-lat1:2.5.17\" target=\"_blank\">Cicero, In Verrem 5.16-17\u003C/a> describes an accusation of Verres regarding a slave who held the role of magister pecoris, of a rich Panhormus citizen called Apollonius Geminus. Varro (Res Rustica 1.2.14), like Cicero, uses the term 'magister pecoris', and so we should understand the collective singular, pecus, rather than 'pec(orum)'. Whether 'pecus' should be understood to refer to sheep, or cattle, or both, is not clear, as the term can refer to either, and in Varro has the general meaning of head shepherd. On the role, which encompassed the full oversight and maintenance of the animals, see Varro, Res Rusticae 2.10. The name Chius is particularly attested in Rome, Spain and North Africa, usually in a slave, or freedman context (e.g. EDR072606, epitaph of a dispensator from Rome, or EDR136029, a slave in the imperial house, or EDR148068, a sevir Augustalis at Ostia. The name Hesychus is particularly attested at Rome, again primarily in a slave or freedman context; the name is attested in Sicily at Syracuse in several late Roman epitaphs.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Merendino et al. 2025 146-147, fig.10.24 \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> \u003Cp>Elegant letters, of a regular size, tending to a slightly curving form, with M and A tending towards cursive forms. I in line 1 and Y in line 3 both extravagant and tall. Use of elegant hederae.\u003C/p> Line 1-4  25  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[161,164,167,170,173,175,178,181,184],{"id":162,"html":163},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: #JP\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Chio\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Chio\">Chio\u003C/span>\u003C/span> ❦ mag(no) mag(istri) \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>pec(oris) ❦ vix(it) ❦ an(nos) ❦ XXXV \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Hesychus\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Hesychus\">Hesychus\u003C/span>\u003C/span> ❦ disp(ensator) \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>fecit \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: #JP\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Chio\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Chio\">CHIO\u003C/span>\u003C/span>❦MAGMAG\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>PEC❦VIX❦AN❦XXXV\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Hesychus\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Hesychus\">HESYCHUS\u003C/span>\u003C/span>❦DISP\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>FECIT\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":165,"html":166},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001693_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo (c) Soprintendenza per i Beni Culturali e Ambientali di Enna\" src=\"ISic001693_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001693.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo (c) Soprintendenza per i Beni Culturali e Ambientali di Enna\" src=\"ISic001693-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":168,"html":169},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text from photograph\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":171,"html":172},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>For Chius, chief overseer of the herds. He lived 35 years. Hesychus the steward made it.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":171,"html":174},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>",{"id":176,"html":177},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>A similar text, a funerary epitaph for Abdalas, magnus magister ovium (i.e. sheep) (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000628\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000628\u003C/a>) was found some 16 km SE of this site. Abdalas was a slave of Domitia Longina, wife of the Emperor Domitian, and a similar context, of either imperial estates or another elite wealthy landowner is likely. \u003Ca href=\"http://data.perseus.org/citations/urn:cts:latinLit:phi0474.phi005.perseus-lat1:2.5.17\" target=\"_blank\">Cicero, In Verrem 5.16-17\u003C/a> describes an accusation of Verres regarding a slave who held the role of magister pecoris, of a rich Panhormus citizen called Apollonius Geminus. Varro (Res Rustica 1.2.14), like Cicero, uses the term 'magister pecoris', and so we should understand the collective singular, pecus, rather than 'pec(orum)'. Whether 'pecus' should be understood to refer to sheep, or cattle, or both, is not clear, as the term can refer to either, and in Varro has the general meaning of head shepherd. On the role, which encompassed the full oversight and maintenance of the animals, see Varro, Res Rusticae 2.10. The name Chius is particularly attested in Rome, Spain and North Africa, usually in a slave, or freedman context (e.g. EDR072606, epitaph of a dispensator from Rome, or EDR136029, a slave in the imperial house, or EDR148068, a sevir Augustalis at Ostia. The name Hesychus is particularly attested at Rome, again primarily in a slave or freedman context; the name is attested in Sicily at Syracuse in several late Roman epitaphs.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":179,"html":180},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Merendino et al. 2025 146-147, fig.10.24 \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":182,"html":183},"handnote"," \u003Cp>Elegant letters, of a regular size, tending to a slightly curving form, with M and A tending towards cursive forms. I in line 1 and Y in line 3 both extravagant and tall. Use of elegant hederae.\u003C/p> Line 1-4  25  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":185,"html":186},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[188,190,193,194],{"html":189},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: #JP",{"id":191,"lang":116,"html":192},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Chio\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Chio\">Chio\u003C/span>\u003C/span> ❦ mag(no) mag(istri) \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>pec(oris) ❦ vix(it) ❦ an(nos) ❦ XXXV \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Hesychus\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Hesychus\">Hesychus\u003C/span>\u003C/span> ❦ disp(ensator) \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>fecit \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":189},{"id":195,"lang":116,"html":196},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Chio\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Chio\">CHIO\u003C/span>\u003C/span>❦MAGMAG\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>PEC❦VIX❦AN❦XXXV\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Hesychus\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Hesychus\">HESYCHUS\u003C/span>\u003C/span>❦DISP\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>FECIT\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[198,200],{"image":102,"thumb":199,"title":105},"ISic001693_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":201,"thumb":202,"title":105},"ISic001693.jpg","ISic001693-thumb.jpg",[204],{"html":60},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Funerary urn for Chius\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic001693\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001693\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Enna\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"store\">Soprintendenza per i Beni Culturali e Ambientali di Enna\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"la\">Latin\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\n                                    \u003Cp>A globular marble urn, with moulded foot and two shoulder handles partially in a 'twisted rope' style, with a plain domed lid. The urn is not otherwise decorated, besides the inscription on one face.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.marble\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">marble\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.urn\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/78\">urn\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\u003C!-- approx measurements taken from photograph -->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">c.45\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">c.40\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">\u003C/depth> \n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.complete\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Four lines, approximately centred on one side of the body of the urn\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.complete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\n                                \u003Cp>Elegant letters, of a regular size, tending to a slightly curving form, with M and A tending towards cursive forms. I in line 1 and Y in line 3 both extravagant and tall. Use of elegant hederae.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line4\">Line 1-4\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\">25\u003C/height>\u003C!-- approx, from scaled photograph -->\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\">\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\"/>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/8977891\">Cuticchi\u003C/placeName>\n                                \u003Cgeo>37.5454, 14.51691\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0051\" notAfter-custom=\"0151\" evidence=\"archaeological-context textual-context\">The necropolis material dates C1 CE to mid-C2 CE; the lettering is more likely C2 CE\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" when=\"2022\">Found in archaeological excavation of a rural settlement and extensive necropolis in the area of contrada Cuticchi (in the context of railway construction work). The urn was found in situ in T.16, a fossa burial ,covered with terracotta slabs.\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">None.\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                    \u003Cchange when=\"2025-12-17\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag created file from publication\u003C/change> \n                \u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic001693_tiled.tif\" height=\"1147px\" width=\"999px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo (c) Soprintendenza per i Beni Culturali e Ambientali di Enna\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic001693.jpg\" height=\"1147px\" width=\"999px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo (c) Soprintendenza per i Beni Culturali e Ambientali di Enna\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n           \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"la\" resp=\"#JP\" source=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>Chio\u003C/name>\u003C/persName> \u003Cg ref=\"#ivy-leaf\">❦\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>mag\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>no\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>mag\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>istri\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>pec\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>oris\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#ivy-leaf\">❦\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>vix\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>it\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#ivy-leaf\">❦\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>an\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>nos\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#ivy-leaf\">❦\u003C/g> \u003Cnum value=\"35\">XXXV\u003C/num>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>Hesychus\u003C/name>\u003C/persName> \u003Cg ref=\"#ivy-leaf\">❦\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>disp\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ensator\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"4\"/>fecit\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\n                        \u003Cnote>Text from photograph\u003C/note>\n                    \u003C/app>\n                    \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>For Chius, chief overseer of the herds. He lived 35 years. Hesychus the steward made it.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n                \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"it\">\n                    \u003Cp>\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>A similar text, a funerary epitaph for Abdalas, magnus magister ovium (i.e. sheep) (\u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000628\">ISic000628\u003C/ref>) was found some 16 km SE of this site. Abdalas was a slave of Domitia Longina, wife of the Emperor Domitian, and a similar context, of either imperial estates or another elite wealthy landowner is likely. \u003Cref target=\"http://data.perseus.org/citations/urn:cts:latinLit:phi0474.phi005.perseus-lat1:2.5.17\">Cicero, In Verrem 5.16-17\u003C/ref> describes an accusation of Verres regarding a slave who held the role of magister pecoris, of a rich Panhormus citizen called Apollonius Geminus. Varro (Res Rustica 1.2.14), like Cicero, uses the term 'magister pecoris', and so we should understand the collective singular, pecus, rather than 'pec(orum)'. Whether 'pecus' should be understood to refer to sheep, or cattle, or both, is not clear, as the term can refer to either, and in Varro has the general meaning of head shepherd. On the role, which encompassed the full oversight and maintenance of the animals, see Varro, Res Rusticae 2.10. The name Chius is particularly attested in Rome, Spain and North Africa, usually in a slave, or freedman context (e.g. EDR072606, epitaph of a dispensator from Rome, or EDR136029, a slave in the imperial house, or EDR148068, a sevir Augustalis at Ostia. The name Hesychus is particularly attested at Rome, again primarily in a slave or freedman context; the name is attested in Sicily at Syracuse in several late Roman epitaphs.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Merendino et al.\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2025\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>146-147, fig.10.24\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/CM7T8P48\"/>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
